p: essential oil was analyzed using gas chromatography and mass spectrometry to fraction into terpene and terpenoid. Fifty two compounds, including hydrocarbons of the oil; α-pinene (10.2%), α-cedrene (9.6%) aromadendrene (4.4%), β-caryophyllene (4.2%), and limonene (3.8%), neryl acetate (11.5%), 2-methylcyclohexyl pentanoate (8.3%), 2-methylcyclohexyl octanoate (4.8%), and geranyl acetate (4.7%) were identified (Mastelic et al. 2017).
